  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\n<!-- Is your feature request related to a specific problem? Is it just a crazy idea? Tell us about it! -->\r\nAdd mechanism to get ERC20Snapshot `balanceOfAt` using block number, as current implementation uses snapshot ID which isn't usable unless snapshot ID is known by contracts.\r\n\r\nThis would allow onchain governance projects to more easily use ERC20Snapshot.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n<!-- Please describe your feature request in detail. -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Make sure that you have reviewed the OpenZeppelin Contributor Guidelines. -->\r\n<!-- https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md -->\r\nThe current implementation of `ERC20Snapshot` exposes a function [`balanceOfAt`](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/90ed1af972299070f51bf4665a85da56ac4d355e/contracts/token/ERC20/ERC20Snapshot.sol#L92) that requires a `snapshotId` instead of [`_blockNumber`](https://github.com/Giveth/minime/blob/ea04d950eea153a04c51fa510b068b9dded390cb/contracts/MiniMeToken.sol#L283) as in the original `minime` token. As a consequence, these snapshots are not accessible by smart contracts which have no idea about the snapshot ID. Furthermore these external contracts also don't have a way of looking for them as the `_accountBalanceSnapshots` are private.\r\n\r\nSince this would enable a larger amount of on-chain governance projects to leverage this feature I would suggest to add a function which implements the binary search and takes a block number similar to minime.\r\n\r\nInitially raised in the forum: https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/erc20-snapshot-not-usable-for-smart-contracts/5310",
